Sentencas: Yttria (8 mol%) stabilized zirconia (8YSZ) photocurable slurry is the basis for stereolithography-based 3D (SLA) printed structured electrolyte support for monolithic solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stack.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry

Sentencas: The curing resin with trifunctional trimethylolpropane triacrylate and 1,6-hexanediol diacrylate (TMPTA/HDDA) mass ratio of 1.5:8.5 and 1 wt% of photoinitiator provided excellent curing performance and low viscosity of 2.1 mPa.s.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry

Sentencas: Stable 8YSZ photocurable slurry possessing high solid content of 43 vol% and low viscosity of 3.6 Pa.s at 30 s-1 shear rate were obtained, without particle sedimentation after 180-day stability test.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry

Sentencas: The activation energy of 8YSZ fabricated by 3D printing method was 0.87 eV, similar to that by dry-pressing method.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry

Sentencas: The 3D printed monolithic 3-tube SOFC stack exhibited a peak power density of 230 mW.cm(-2) at 850 ?.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry

Sentencas: This research proves the great potential of 3D printing technology to prepare monolithic SOFC stack, paving the way to develop SOFCs for practical applications.
Titulo: A new and simple way to prepare monolithic solid oxide fuel cell stack by stereolithography 3D printing technology using 8 mol% yttria stabilized zirconia photocurable slurry
